From: Andrew Honig <ahonig@google.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jan 2018 10:12:03 -0800
Subject: KVM: x86: Add memory barrier on vmcs field lookup
Git-commit: 75f139aaf896d6fdeec2e468ddfa4b2fe469bf40
Patch-mainline: v4.15-rc8
References: bsc#1068032 CVE-2017-5753

This adds a memory barrier when performing a lookup into
the vmcs_field_to_offset_table.  This is related to
CVE-2017-5753.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Honig <ahonig@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Jim Mattson <jmattson@google.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c |   12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
@@ -877,8 +877,16 @@ static inline short vmcs_field_to_offset
 {
 	BUILD_BUG_ON(ARRAY_SIZE(vmcs_field_to_offset_table) > SHRT_MAX);
 
-	if (field >= ARRAY_SIZE(vmcs_field_to_offset_table) ||
-	    vmcs_field_to_offset_table[field] == 0)
+	if (field >= ARRAY_SIZE(vmcs_field_to_offset_table))
+		return -ENOENT;
+
+	/*
+	 * FIXME: Mitigation for CVE-2017-5753.  To be replaced with a
+	 * generic mechanism.
+	 */
+	asm("lfence");
+
+	if (vmcs_field_to_offset_table[field] == 0)
 		return -ENOENT;
 
 	return vmcs_field_to_offset_table[field];
